      "whyWatch": "Turkey are making their first appearance in 24 years where they made it all the way to the semifinals en route to a third-place finish. They were considered as dark horses in Euro 2020 and 2024. They certainly did not live up to the billing in the former, losing all three group games and scoring only one goal. In the latter, they made it to the quarterfinals, and were unlucky to lose against the Netherlands. The Socceroos will not be an easy opponent as they have a strong defensive spine coupled with exciting young attackers in Mo Toure and Nestory Irakunda.",
