      "awayTeamKey": "japan",
      "matchImportance": 5,
      "rivalryScore": 5,
      "whyWatch": "Whisper it quietly, but Japan seem to have changed their mindset of being happy to be a perennial participant, into one that is seeking to be considered as a serious contender. A positive start against the Netherlands will only strengthen their credentials. The Netherlands are not the Netherlands of yore where Johann Cruyff, Ruud Gullit, Marco van Basten, or Dennis Bergkamp play a scintillating style of football. It remains to be seen whether a more functional approach championed by Ronald Koeman will lead to a World Cup glory for the Oranje.",
      "kickoffUTC": "2026-06-14T20:00:00Z",
