      "matchImportance": 5,
      "rivalryScore": 3,
      "whyWatch": "The team that won none of their games in the group stage but still made it to the World Cup play-offs by virtue of  their Nations League performance, Sweden could well be a team to keep an eye on. They have two top strikers in Alexander Isak and Viktor Gyokeres, though they had contrasting fortunes last season. Gyokeres helped Arsenal won their first Premier League title in 22 years and made it all the way to the Champions League final, while Isak struggled with injuries and barely made an impact after a record breaking summer move to Liverpool. Tunisia did not concede a goal in qualifying, but this is a rather inexperienced squad, which might struggle in this stage.",
      "kickoffUTC": "2026-06-15T02:00:00Z"
